  "prompt": "What are some definition-based questions that represent only one-word answers?",
  "response": "Here are some definition-based questions that can be answered with a single word:\n\n1. What is the capital of France?\n   - **Answer:** Paris\n\n2. What do you call a young horse?\n   - **Answer:** Foal\n\n3. What is the chemical symbol for gold?\n   - **Answer:** Au\n\n4. What is the term for an animal that primarily eats plants?\n   - **Answer:** Herbivore\n\n5. What is the process by which plants make their food using sunlight?\n   - **Answer:** Photosynthesis\n\n6. What is the term for a \u062b\u0644\u0627\u062b\u064a \u0627\u0644\u0623\u0628\u0639\u0627\u062f representation of something?\n   - **Answer:** Model\n\n7. What do you call a group of stars?\n   - **Answer:** Galaxy\n\n8. What is the name of the language primarily spoken in Brazil?\n   - **Answer:** Portuguese\n\n9. What is the main ingredient in guacamole?\n   - **Answer:** Avocado\n\n10. What is the unit of currency in Japan?\n   - **Answer:** Yen\n\nThese questions are designed to elicit straightforward, one-word responses.",
